1 0 0 1 72 760 Tm
(# agentcontainer Whitepaper) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 746 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 732 Tm
(## Abstract) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 718 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 704 Tm
(agentcontainer is a transport and execution substrate for mobile software agents represented) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 690 Tm
(as authenticated Python source files. Each agent carries its own identity and secret, can be) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 676 Tm
(deployed as live code into a remote TCP container, and can later clone or move across a) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 662 Tm
(federated tree of containers. The container provides operating primitives, not an) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 648 Tm
(opinionated LLM backend. This decoupling allows agents to remain autonomous in their choice) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 634 Tm
(of reasoning engines and external APIs.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 620 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 606 Tm
(## 1. Problem Statement) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 592 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 578 Tm
(Modern AI systems are usually centralized around a fixed inference endpoint and a) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 564 Tm
(server-side orchestration layer. That model is effective for many SaaS architectures, but it) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 550 Tm
(is less effective for environments where:) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 536 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 522 Tm
(- data is physically distributed across departments, labs, or edge nodes;) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 508 Tm
(- movement of lightweight logic is cheaper than movement of entire datasets;) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 494 Tm
(- agents need local system access near the data they inspect;) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 480 Tm
(- operators want a neutral substrate instead of a monolithic "AI platform".) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 466 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 452 Tm
(agentcontainer addresses this by defining a node that accepts authenticated Python agents as) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 438 Tm
(text, loads them dynamically, and gives them a set of explicit host primitives for file) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 424 Tm
(access, process execution, HTTP egress, and mobility.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 410 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 396 Tm
(## 2. Design Principles) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 382 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 368 Tm
(The system follows five principles.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 354 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 340 Tm
(First, every message is explicitly authenticated. Authentication is part of the application) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 326 Tm
(payload model, not an external session.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 312 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 298 Tm
(Second, the agent is the portable unit. The source file is not merely a script uploaded to a) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 284 Tm
(server; it is the identity-bearing artifact that can survive relocation.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 270 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 256 Tm
(Third, the container is intentionally neutral regarding LLM providers. Agents may call) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 242 Tm
(external reasoning services, but the container itself does not own the model contract.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 228 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 214 Tm
(Fourth, federation is hierarchical. A tree is operationally simpler than a full mesh and) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 200 Tm
(maps well to organizations such as departments, labs, and workstations.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 186 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 172 Tm
(Fifth, the first implementation should optimize for conceptual clarity. Stronger isolation,) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 158 Tm
(policy, and cryptographic identity can be layered later.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 144 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 130 Tm
(## 3. System Model) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 116 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 102 Tm
(An agentcontainer node exposes a TCP port. Clients and agents send JSON Lines messages. Each) Tj
ET
