1 0 0 1 72 564 Tm
(## 4. Mobility Semantics) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 550 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 536 Tm
(Mobility is expressed by two primitives.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 522 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 508 Tm
(Clone creates a new live copy of the current agent on another node while preserving the) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 494 Tm
(current local instance.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 480 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 466 Tm
(Move serializes the current source code and deploys it to another node, then removes the) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 452 Tm
(local instance after successful activation on the destination.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 438 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 424 Tm
(In both cases, the agent source is re-sent as text over the protocol. The destination node) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 410 Tm
(does not need shared state with the source node beyond the authenticated message it) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 396 Tm
(receives.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 382 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 368 Tm
(## 5. Federation) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 354 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 340 Tm
(Federation is represented as a tree. Each node knows its children through static) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 326 Tm
(configuration. The runtime exposes a networks primitive so that an agent can inspect the) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 312 Tm
(currently configured topology and decide how to traverse it. A tree structure is sufficient) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 298 Tm
(for many enterprise or laboratory deployments where containers are arranged by office, team,) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 284 Tm
(department, or rack.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 270 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 256 Tm
(## 6. Reasoning and External LLMs) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 242 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 228 Tm
(The system deliberately separates orchestration from inference. agentcontainer is not an LLM) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 214 Tm
(gateway. Instead, an agent can hold its own API secret and directly call an external) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 200 Tm
(reasoning service through the host HTTP primitive or its own imported libraries. This) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 186 Tm
(separation prevents the container from becoming a bottleneck for model selection, key) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 172 Tm
(management, or provider-specific assumptions.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 158 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 144 Tm
(## 7. Security Discussion) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 130 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 72 116 Tm
(The implemented base offers message integrity and straightforward authentication, but it) Tj
1 0 0 1 72 102 Tm
(does not claim hardened isolation. Dynamic Python execution is inherently powerful and) Tj
